\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 A Namespace in Kubernetes is a way to logically partition or isolate resources within a single Kubernetes cluster.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 A namespace is like a folder inside your Kubernetes cluster.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Inside this folder, you can keep:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Pods
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Services
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Deployments
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ConfigMaps
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Secrets
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 PVCs
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 etc.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Even though everything is running in one cluster, namespaces logically separate the resources.
