\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 
A Volume in Kubernetes is a storage resource that is mounted inside a Pod to persist or share data among containers. Volumes solve the problem of ephemeral container storage by providing a dedicated space that can survive container restarts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf6\kerning0\insrsid3440241 \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Why Volumes are Needed?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf1\kerning0\insrsid3440241 
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 By default, containers use a wr\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 itable layer in their filesystem.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Data written here is lost when:
\par \tab \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 The container restarts.
\par \tab \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 The Pod is deleted.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 To persist data, share data between containers, or maintain state across restarts, Kubernetes uses Volumes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf6\kerning0\insrsid3440241 \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Where is Data Stored if No Volume is Defined?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf1\kerning0\insrsid3440241 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Stored in the container\hich\f1 \rquote \loch\f1 s writable layer inside the container filesystem.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Physically, it is located on the Node's local disk, managed by the container runtime, e.g.:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Docker: /var/lib/docker/containers/<container-id>/
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Containerd: /var/lib/co\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ntainerd/
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Limitations:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Data is lost if the Pod is deleted.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Node crashes or reboots may clean up the storage.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Data cannot be shared between containers in different Pods.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf6\kerning0\insrsid3440241 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Container filesystem vs Volume:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf1\kerning0\insrsid3440241 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1  Without Volumes  => Data lost on container restart
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1  With Volumes => Data survives container restart within the Pod, can be shared, and can be made persistent with PVC+PV
\par ---------------------------------
