\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs28\cf6\kerning0\insrsid3440241 \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 PV => Persistent Volume}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf1\kerning0\insrsid3440241 \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 :
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 A Persistent Volume (PV) is a cluster-managed storage resource in Kubernetes that exists independently of any Pod. It provides persistent storage that remains available even if a Pod is de\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 
leted or restarted.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1  Key Features of PV:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Cluster-wide resource: Managed by the cluster \tab administrator.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Independent of Pods: Not tied to the Pod lifecycle.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Where Can a PV Get Its Actual Storage From?
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 A PV does not store data by itself.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 It simply represents storage from an underlying storage system.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 1. hostPath (Local node storage)
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 hostPath:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   \tab path: "/mnt/data"
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 2. NFS (Network File System)
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 nfs:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   server: 10.0.0.10
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   path: /exports/data
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 3. CSI Drivers (Container Storage Interface)
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 csi:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   driver: ebs.c\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 si.aws.com
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   \tab volumeHandle: vol-0abcd1234
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 PV Life Cycle:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 1. Provisioning:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Static: Admin manually creates PVs.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Dynamic: Kubernetes automatically provisions PV based on \tab StorageClass when PVC is created.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 2. Binding: PVC gets bound to a matching PV.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 3. Using: Pod uses PVC, which uses the bound PV.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 4. Reclaim Policy: When PVC is deleted, PV can either:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Retain: Keep data for manual recovery.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Recycle: Wipe and reuse.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Delete: Delete the storage resource
\par ---------------------
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Example:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 apiVersion: v1
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 kind: Pers\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 istentVolume
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 metadata:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   name: example-pv
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 spec:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   capacity:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     storage: 1Gi
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   accessModes:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     - ReadWriteOnce
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   persistentVolumeReclaimPolicy: Retain
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   hostPath:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     path: /mnt/data
\par ---------------------------------------------------------
