\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Here \line Capacity: Defines the size of storage in the PV (e.g., 1Gi).
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 There is no strict maximum or minimum capacity limit defined by \tab Kubernetes itself for a Persistent Volume (PV).
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Capacity Limits Depend On:
\par \tab \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 AWS EBS: 1 GiB to 16 TiB
\par \tab \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 GCP Persistent Disk\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 : 1 GiB to 64 TiB
\par \tab \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Azure Disk: 4 GiB to 64 TiB
\par 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 AccessModes: Defines how the volume can be mounted by Pods:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ReadWriteOnce (RWO): Mounted read-write by one Pod.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ReadWriteOnce (RWO) means Only one node can mount this volume in read-write mode.Multiple pods on the same node can use it.If attempted from another Node, it will fail \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 
 only one Node can have write access.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ReadOnlyMany (ROX): means it can be read by multiple Pods across multiple Nodes at the same time.All Pods can only read the data \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1  no write a\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 
ccess.Useful for sharing common data or configurations across many Pods.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ReadWriteMany (RWX) means Many nodes/pods can read-write at the same time. Useful for shared storage where multiple Pods need to collaborate or write data.
\par ----------------------------------------
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   persistentVolumeReclaimPolicy: Retain
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Defines what happens to the storage when PVC is deleted.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Options:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Retain }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af34\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f34\fs28\cf1\kerning0\insrsid3440241 \loch\af34\dbch\af31505\hich\f34 \u8594\'3f\loch\f34  Keep the data even after PVC deletion (manual \tab \tab \tab 
       cleanup needed).
\par \tab \hich\af34\dbch\af31505\loch\f34 \hich\f34 Recycle (deprecated) \u8594\'3f\loch\f34  Auto clean folder (not used anymore).
\par \tab \hich\af34\dbch\af31505\loch\f34 \hich\f34 Delete \u8594\'3f\loch\f34  Delete the storage (common in cloud volumes).
\par \hich\af34\dbch\af31505\loch\f34 Your policy: Retain
\par \tab \hich\af34\dbch\af31505\loch\f34 Data will remain on disk even if PVC or Po\hich\af34\dbch\af31505\loch\f34 d is deleted.
\par -------------------------------------------------
\par \hich\af34\dbch\af31505\loch\f34   storageClassName: manual
\par \tab \hich\af34\dbch\af31505\loch\f34 Tells Kubernetes which StorageClass this PV belongs to.
\par \tab \hich\af34\dbch\af31505\loch\f34 A PVC with storageClassName: manual will bind to this PV.
\par \hich\af34\dbch\af31505\loch\f34 This is used when doing static provisioning.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf1\kerning0\insrsid3440241 
