\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 A Persistent Volume Claim (PVC) is a user\hich\f1 \rquote \loch\f1 s request for storage in Kubernetes. It abstracts the storage details, allowing developers to request storage without knowing the underlying infrastructure.

\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Key Features of PVC
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Storage request: Specifies size, access mode, and storage class \tab (optional).
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Dynamic or Static binding:
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 If a matching PV exists, it b\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 inds automatically.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 If not, a StorageClass can dynamically provision a PV.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Decouples app and storage: Pods use PVCs instead of directly \tab accessing PVs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf6\kerning0\insrsid3440241 \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Example}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf1\kerning0\insrsid3440241 \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 :
