\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs28\kerning0\highlight7\insrsid3440241 \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 6. ConfigMap}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf1\lang9\langfe16393\kerning0\langnp9\insrsid3440241 
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 A ConfigMap in Kubernetes is used to inject configuration data (non-sensitive data like application properties, environment variables, URLs, etc.) into your applications without hardcoding them into container images.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Instead of rebuilding an image every time configuration changes, you can update the ConfigMap \hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1  keeping code and co\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 nfiguration separate.
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Why Use ConfigMaps?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf1\kerning0\insrsid3440241 \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Avoid hardcoding configuration inside application containers.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Can update config without rebuilding Docker images.
\par \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Supports injecting data as:
\par \tab \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Environment Variables
\par \tab \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Command-line Arguments (not recomented)
\par \tab \tab \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Configuration Files (via volumes)
\par ---------------------------------------------------
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 Example 1:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> nano configmaps.yml
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 apiVersion: v1
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 kind: ConfigMap
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 metadata:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   name: app-config
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 data:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   DB_HOST: localhost
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   DB_PORT: "3306"
\par -------------------------------
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ----> kubectl create -f configmaps.yml
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ----> kubectl get configmap
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ----> kubectl describe configmap app-config
\par -------------------------------
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 How to Use ConfigMap in a Pod:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 As Environment Variables
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> nano pod.yml
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 apiVersion: v1
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 kind: Pod
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 metadata:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   name: configmap-pod
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 spec:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   containers:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   - name: myapp
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     image: busybox
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     command: [ "/bin/sh", "-c", "env; sleep 3600" ]
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     env:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     - name: DB_HOST
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1       valueFrom:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1         configMapKeyRef:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1           name: app-config
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1           key: DB_HOST
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     - na\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 me: DB_PORT
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1       valueFrom:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1         configMapKeyRef:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1           name: app-config
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1           key: DB_PORT
\par -----------------------------------------
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> kubectl reate -f pod.yml
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> kubectl exec -it configmap-pod -- env
\par ------------------------------------------
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> kubectl pod1.yml
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 2. As Volume (Mounted as File):
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 apiVersion: v1
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 kind: Pod
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 metadata:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   name: configmap-pod
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 spec:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   containers:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   - name: myapp
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     image: busybox
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     command: [ "/bin/sh", "-c", "cat /config/DB_HOST; sleep 3600" ]
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     volumeMounts\hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 :
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     - name: config-volume
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1       mountPath: /config
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   volumes:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1   - name: config-volume
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1     configMap:
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1       name: app-config
\par -------------------------------------------
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> kubectl create -f pod1.yml
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> kubectl exec -it configmap-pod -- cat /config/DB_HOST
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> kubectl get configmaps
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> kubectl describe configmap <name>
\par \hich\af1\dbch\af31505\loch\f1 ---> kubectl delete configmap <name>
\par -------------------------------------------
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 \f1\fs28\cf11\kerning0\highlight11\insrsid3440241 ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af1\afs28 \ltrch\fcs0 
